Deploying OmniStudio Components Between Orgs or Migrating to OmniStudio Standard

Deployment means moving OmniStudio components from one org to another, whether you use OmniStudio for Vlocity or OmniStudio Standard. Migration means migrating your data from the OmniStudio for Vlocity custom data model to the Salesforce standard data model and switching to the Salesforce standard runtime. OmniStudio migration includes migration of OmniStudio metadata only.

Move OmniStudio components from a sandbox or dev org to another such as a production org

Use OmniStudio with the standard data model and the Salesforce standard runtime, by migrating from OmniStudio for Vlocity to OmniStudio Standard

Deploying OmniStudio Components Between Orgs
For your projects that use OmniStudio tools, move the components and metadata from one org to another using the Build Tool (formerly known as Vlocity Build Tool or VBT), Salesforce Developer Experience (SDFX), or IDX Workbench. For simple cases, you can move objects between orgs by exporting and importing data packs.

Data Deployment with the OmniStudio Build Tool
The OmniStudio Build Tool is a Node.js command-line automation tool that packages and deploys Salesforce data packs in a source-control-friendly format.

IDX Workbench Desktop Application
IDX Workbench is a desktop application that you use to deploy OmniStudio data packs and Salesforce metadata. 

Migration Process from OmniStudio for Vlocity to OmniStudio Standard

NOTE Migration includes OmniStudio metadata only. If you migrated and you have data from other clouds or calculation matrices, you must separately migrate those components along with OmniStudio metadata. Angular OmniScripts must be rebuilt as Lightning web components.

Data Deployment with Data Packs
A data pack is a collection of components and related functionality that are packaged for deployment between orgs.
